qas.question: What people had a coup around the time Nasser returned to Egypt?
What was Nasser's reaction to the questions he was asked?
What did the interrogation provoke Nasser to do?

context: Nasser's return to Egypt coincided with Husni al-Za'im's <a0_0>Syrian<a0_0/> coup d'état. Its success and evident popular support among the Syrian people encouraged Nasser's revolutionary pursuits. Soon after his return, he was summoned and interrogated by <a1_0>Prime Minister Ibrahim Abdel<a1_0/> Hadi regarding suspicions that he was forming a secret group of dissenting officers. According to secondhand reports, Nasser <a2_0>convincingly denied the allegations<a2_0/>. Abdel Hadi was also hesitant to take drastic measures against the army, especially in front of its chief of staff, who was present during the interrogation, and subsequently released Nasser. The interrogation pushed Nasser to <a3_0>speed up his group's activities<a3_0/>.
